WEBVTT

00:08.061 --> 00:09.495
Isn't this place charming?

00:09.497 --> 00:10.797
As advertised,

00:10.799 --> 00:13.399
but you didn't invite me here
for the charm

00:13.401 --> 00:15.334
or the ice cream.

00:15.336 --> 00:16.602
We can't just have ice cream?

00:16.604 --> 00:17.703
We can,

00:17.705 --> 00:19.438
but not in this instance.

00:19.440 --> 00:21.374
Better chance of being hit
by lightning.

00:21.376 --> 00:23.075
(chuckles)

00:23.077 --> 00:24.944
Okay, I have a problem.

00:24.946 --> 00:26.579
Well,

00:26.581 --> 00:29.315
first of all, your mom's got
a lot on her plate,

00:29.317 --> 00:32.250
and I think she's doing an
outstanding job considering...

00:32.253 --> 00:33.386
It's not about Mom.

00:33.388 --> 00:35.154
Oh.

00:35.156 --> 00:37.356
It's about my teacher.

00:37.358 --> 00:39.425
(phone rings) It's like she's made it
her mission in life

00:39.427 --> 00:41.260
to keep me from ever graduating.

00:41.262 --> 00:42.795
Turn that thing off.

00:42.797 --> 00:44.430
But what if it's important?

00:44.432 --> 00:45.832
Choose.

00:47.668 --> 00:49.836
Look, here's the problem.

00:49.838 --> 00:52.371
She's notorious for being harder
on the girls,

00:52.373 --> 00:54.707
but when she found out
I was from a family of cops...

00:54.709 --> 00:56.008
Look, I should really check it.

00:56.010 --> 00:57.577
Choose.

00:57.579 --> 00:58.945
(door opens, bell dings)

00:58.947 --> 01:00.179
Grandpa...

01:00.181 --> 01:02.782
How would you feel if I was
constantly interrupting?

01:02.784 --> 01:05.318
Deputy Commissioner Moore
just walked in.

01:05.319 --> 01:07.520
(bell dings)

01:11.625 --> 01:13.826
Hold that thought.

01:18.699 --> 01:20.867
A cop's been shot.

01:22.970 --> 01:24.737
(sighs)
Who and where?

01:24.739 --> 01:26.272
North End bus yard,

01:26.274 --> 01:27.673
multiple precincts rolled,

01:27.675 --> 01:29.876
but radio chatter's not clear
on a name,

01:29.878 --> 01:31.510
how bad they're hit.

01:31.512 --> 01:33.179
We've got conflicting
descriptions

01:33.181 --> 01:35.114
of perps and
direction of flight.

01:35.116 --> 01:38.150
Tell me something we do know.

01:38.152 --> 01:39.819
Whoever's down

01:39.821 --> 01:42.588
is a detective
out of Danny's precinct.

01:43.423 --> 01:44.957
(sighs)

01:44.959 --> 01:46.893
DANNY:
<i>This is Detective Reagan.</i>

01:46.895 --> 01:48.194
Leave a message.

01:48.196 --> 01:49.462
Hey, Danny, it's me;
give me a call.

01:49.464 --> 01:50.730
Let me know everything's okay.

01:50.732 --> 01:53.432
Hey, voice mail again?

01:53.434 --> 01:55.167
Yeah, third time.
You heard anything new?

01:55.169 --> 01:56.602
Lady called 911,

01:56.604 --> 01:58.170
said she was out
walking her dog,

01:58.172 --> 01:59.672
heard yelling
from behind a fence.

01:59.674 --> 02:02.108
Someone being accused
of being a cop.

02:02.110 --> 02:03.309
Shots fired.

02:03.311 --> 02:04.477
There's still no name?

02:04.479 --> 02:06.312
Only that he was rushed
to St. Benjamin's.

02:06.314 --> 02:07.813
A couple of guys
are headed over.

02:07.815 --> 02:09.315
All right, I'm gonna ask
the boss if we can, too,

02:09.317 --> 02:11.117
just in case, all right?
Okay, come on,

02:11.119 --> 02:13.419
there's got to be 15
detectives in the 5-4 squad.

02:13.421 --> 02:15.655
(phone ringing)
Odds are it isn't your brother.

02:15.657 --> 02:17.123
Danny's wife.

02:17.125 --> 02:18.624
No way she's heard anything.

02:18.626 --> 02:20.259
Unless she got the call.

02:20.261 --> 02:21.460
Hey, Linda.

02:21.462 --> 02:23.930
Jamie, it's not Danny.

02:23.932 --> 02:25.564
He called you?

02:25.566 --> 02:27.266
Yeah, in case I heard,
but he's fine.

02:27.268 --> 02:29.302
He's working a case
in Murray Hill,

02:29.304 --> 02:30.670
and he said he was gonna
call your dad

02:30.672 --> 02:31.938
as soon as he hung up with me.

02:31.940 --> 02:32.972
Thank God.

02:32.974 --> 02:34.206
Yeah, no kidding.

02:34.208 --> 02:35.441
Listen...

02:35.443 --> 02:37.543
Hi, Mom!
Awesome!

02:37.545 --> 02:39.312
Yeah, I'm picking the boys up
right now,

02:39.314 --> 02:40.913
so could you call
Erin and Henry?

02:40.915 --> 02:42.615
You know, make sure
they're not worried, too.

02:42.617 --> 02:43.783
Yeah, they already are.

02:43.785 --> 02:45.284
Thanks, Linda.

02:45.286 --> 02:47.853
(panting)

02:47.855 --> 02:50.022
(groans)

02:52.059 --> 02:54.193
(sighs)

02:56.063 --> 02:58.030
I'm glad it wasn't Danny.

02:58.032 --> 03:00.333
There, I said it.

03:00.335 --> 03:03.169
I felt the same way.

03:03.171 --> 03:04.303
Danny's family.

03:04.305 --> 03:07.039
Steve Tomlin has one, too.

03:07.041 --> 03:09.308
Let's hope for the best.

03:10.744 --> 03:11.978
Dino says

03:11.980 --> 03:13.879
Steve has been undercover
for the last year,

03:13.881 --> 03:16.082
working his way up the chain
of a drug operation

03:16.084 --> 03:18.351
run by Santo Castillo.

03:18.353 --> 03:20.186
Somebody made him.

03:20.188 --> 03:22.455
Word is,
after Castillo shot him,

03:22.457 --> 03:24.690
Steve managed to put
a slug in Castillo,

03:24.692 --> 03:25.891
who ran off.

03:25.893 --> 03:28.561
Tough cop.

03:28.563 --> 03:30.963
Gave him the Combat Cross
in '09.

03:30.965 --> 03:33.165
(door opens)

03:36.670 --> 03:38.704
Commissioner?

03:38.706 --> 03:41.140
How's my officer?

03:41.142 --> 03:43.175
Um, I'm afraid he's gone.

03:43.177 --> 03:45.478
Three bullets,
one through the carotid.

03:45.480 --> 03:49.482
He lost too much blood
by the time he arrived.

03:50.417 --> 03:52.618
Thank you, Doctor.

04:00.394 --> 04:03.462
I'll need to talk to his wife.

04:03.464 --> 04:04.864
Lorraine.

04:04.866 --> 04:06.966
Married to Steve for 22 years,

04:06.968 --> 04:08.401
tax accountant by trade.

04:08.403 --> 04:10.603
They have a home
in Staten Island.

04:12.706 --> 04:14.807
Frank, she's here.

04:16.000 --> 04:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:26.386 --> 04:28.854
Two daughters,
Bella and Lucy,

04:28.856 --> 04:31.023
both in college.

04:38.432 --> 04:40.599
Mrs. Tomlin?

04:42.302 --> 04:44.403
I'm so sorry.

04:48.575 --> 04:52.478
Can I arrange to get Lucy
and Bella home from school?

04:52.480 --> 04:54.880
Oh, that, uh...

04:54.882 --> 04:56.715
Uh, yes.

04:56.717 --> 04:59.285
Um, thank you.

04:59.287 --> 05:01.620
My department owes Steve

05:01.622 --> 05:05.224
a deep debt of gratitude
for his years of service.

05:05.226 --> 05:07.259
Anything we can do to help,

05:07.261 --> 05:09.195
you only need to ask.

05:09.197 --> 05:12.765
Catch whoever murdered
my husband.

05:14.167 --> 05:16.569
We will do that.

05:18.886 --> 05:22.886
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Blue Bloods 4x21 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Above and Beyond</font>
Original Air Date on May 2, 2014

05:22.911 --> 05:27.911
